      • copyOriginalMap

        @NonNull
protected java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V> copyOriginalMap()
        Description copied from class: CopyOnWriteMap
        Returns a copy of CopyOnWriteMap.originalMap() used the first time a mutating method is called on this class.

        The default implementation creates the new map using CopyOnWriteMap.createEmptyMap(int) and adds members using Map.putAll(java.util.Map<? extends K, ? extends V>).

        Subclasses may override this method to return other map types or use a different copying technique.

        Overrides:
        copyOriginalMap in class CopyOnWriteMap<K,V>

      • createEmptyMap

        @NonNull
protected java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V> createEmptyMap(int capacity)
        Creates an empty map with specified initial capacity.

        This implementation returns a new ConcurrentSkipListMap if the originalMap() is a SortedMap and otherwise returns a new ConcurrentHashMap.

        Subclasses may override this method to return other map types.

        Overrides:
        createEmptyMap in class CopyOnWriteMap<K,V>

      • readOnlyMap

        @NonNull
protected java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V> readOnlyMap()
        Description copied from class: CopyOnWriteMap
        Returns map for use in implementing read-only operations. This will not trigger a copy. Use CopyOnWriteMap.mutableMap() for mutating operations.

        Note that if CopyOnWriteMap.wasCopied() is true, this will return the same object as CopyOnWriteMap.mutableMap().

        Overrides:
        readOnlyMap in class CopyOnWriteMap<K,V>

      • mutableMap

        @NonNull
protected java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V> mutableMap()
        Description copied from class: CopyOnWriteMap
        Returns map for use in implementing mutating operations. This will trigger a copy of the CopyOnWriteMap.originalMap() (synchronized against this object) the first time it is invoked after construction or after call to CopyOnWriteMap.revertToOriginalMap(). Use CopyOnWriteMap.readOnlyMap() for read-only operations.
        Overrides:
        mutableMap in class CopyOnWriteMap<K,V>
